1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d6 4. O-O Bd7 {This is Black's best move. After
practically any other move, we can play c3-d4:} (4... e5 5. c3) (4... e6 5. c3)
(4... h6 5. c3) (4... Qc7 5. c3) 5. Re1 Nf6 6. c3 g6 $2 {Surrendering the
centre to White for no compensation!} (6... a6 $1) 7. d4 $16 Bg7 8. h3 {
Comparatively slow, but not bad.} O-O (8... e5 {This is maybe blundering a
pawn, but we are interested in a strategic solution...?} 9. dxc5 $1 dxc5 10. a4
a6 11. Bf1 O-O 12. Na3 $14 {[%csl Ga3,Rd5][%cal Ya3c4,Ya3c2,Yc2e3,Yc4e3] This
position very much resembles a Torre System with 2...g6.}) 9. dxc5 $1 dxc5 10.
a4 {A necessary part of our plan.} ({Black is fine after} 10. Na3 a6 11. Bf1 b5
{followed by ...c4, when our f1-bishop is restricted.}) 10... e5 11. Bg5 $14 {
Later, White managed to exploit Black's weaknesses on the d-file.} Qc7 12. Na3
Rad8 13. Qc2 a6 14. Bf1 h6 15. Be3 Na5 16. Nd2 Rc8 17. Red1 Rfd8 18. Nac4 Nxc4
19. Nxc4 Bc6 20. Nd2 a5 21. Bb5 b6 22. Bxc6 Qxc6 23. Qb3 Rb8 24. Nc4 Re8 25.
Rd6 1-0

