1. Nf3 c5 2. e4 Nc6 3. Bb5 d6 4. O-O Bd7 5. c3 (5. Re1 Nf6 6. c3 {is our
preferred move order.}) 5... Nf6 6. Re1 g6 $2 {This is too passive.} 7. h3 $5
$16 ({The direct} 7. d4 $1 {was even stronger. For example} cxd4 8. cxd4 {After
} a6 {White has more than one way to get an advantage:} 9. Bxc6 $5 $16 {
After ...a6, we usually take on c6 in the Rossolimo unless theory tells us
something different!} (9. Bc4 $16) (9. Ba4 $16) 9... bxc6 (9... Bxc6 10. Nc3
Bg7 11. d5 Bd7 12. e5 $1 {This is the computer solution.} ({In general I would
prefer} 12. h3 O-O 13. Be3 $14) 12... dxe5 13. Nxe5 O-O 14. Qb3 $16) 10. h3 $1
Bg7 11. Nc3 O-O 12. Bf4 $16 {Black has the pair of bishop but his problem is
that the d7-bishop cannot be developed to a good square.} ({We will examine} 
12. e5 {but if we have the slightest doubts about it, go for simple and solid
development.})) 7... Bg7 8. d4 a6 (8... cxd4 9. cxd4 O-O 10. Nc3 a6 11. Bxc6
Bxc6 (11... bxc6 12. Bf4 $14) 12. d5 Bd7 13. Be3 Rc8 14. Bd4 $14) 9. Bf1 $1 (9.
Bxc6 $1 Bxc6 10. d5 Bd7 11. e5 dxe5 12. Nxe5 O-O 13. c4 e6 14. Nc3 exd5 15.
cxd5 {also leads to an advantage for White.}) 9... cxd4 (9... e5 $2 {How
should White continue here?} 10. dxc5 $1 {Exactly - if Black's bishop is on g7,
we generally take on e5.} ({After closing the position with} 10. d5 $2 {
Black can prepare counterplay with ...f5.} Ne7 11. c4 O-O 12. Nc3 Ne8 $132 {
[%cal Gf7f5]}) 10... dxc5 11. a4 O-O {Now, we decide between Bg5 and Na3.} 12.
Bg5 {This is more flexible - White also keeps the option of continuing with
Nbd2.} (12. Na3) 12... Qc7 13. Nbd2 Be6 14. Bc4 Bxc4 15. Nxc4 b5 16. Bxf6 Bxf6
17. Ne3 $14 {[%csl Rd5,Ge3][%cal Ye3d5]}) 10. cxd4 O-O ({White has the
advantage after} 10... d5 11. e5 Ne4 {, now both ways to exchange the
e4-knight are good:} 12. Nbd2 (12. Nc3 $5 Nxc3 13. bxc3 $14) 12... Nxd2 13.
Bxd2 Qb6 14. Bc3 O-O 15. Qd2 Bf5 16. Nh4 $16) 11. Nc3 h6 (11... e5 12. dxe5
dxe5 13. Bc4 $5 $14 (13. Bg5 $14) (13. Be3 $14) 13... b5 14. Bb3) 12. Be3 e6
13. e5 Ne8 14. Bf4 dxe5 (14... d5 15. Qd2 Kh7 16. Bd3 (16. Rac1)) 15. dxe5 Qe7
16. Ne4 b6 17. a3 Nc7 18. Nf6+ Bxf6 19. exf6 Qd8 20. Bxh6 Re8 21. Bg7 Bc8 22.
Qc1 Qd5 23. Rd1 Qc5 24. b4 Qxc1 25. Raxc1 Bb7 26. Rc4 g5 27. Nxg5 Nd5 28. Rh4
1-0

