{A great game by White in the dubious yet often played 5...a6?! variation!} 1.
e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nc6 4. O-O Bd7 5. Re1 a6 $6 {This is bad in this
particular position.} (5... Nf6 $1) 6. Bxc6 $1 Bxc6 7. d4 cxd4 8. Nxd4 {
White has some advantage — we will follow up with c4 to gain a positional
advantage or go for fast development with Nc3, Bg5, etc.} Bd7 (8... Rc8 9. c4 (
9. Bg5) 9... Nf6 10. Nc3) 9. c4 (9. Bg5 $5 Qb6 10. Nc3) 9... Nf6 10. Nc3 {
White has an excellent version of a Maroczy Bind.} Rc8 11. Qe2 (11. b3 b5 12.
Bg5 $5 $16) 11... Qc7 12. b3 e5 ({Black cannot play} 12... b5 {due to} 13. Nd5
$1 (13. Bb2 $5 bxc4 14. Rac1) (13. Bg5 $1 bxc4 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. Nd5 $18) 13...
Nxd5 14. cxd5 {Black is too far behind with his development.} g6 (14... e5 15.
dxe6 fxe6 16. Bb2 (16. Bg5) 16... Be7 17. Qg4 $18) 15. Bb2 Bg7 $140 16. Ne6 $18
) 13. Nf5 Qc6 (13... Bxf5 14. exf5 b5 15. Bg5 $1 bxc4 16. Bxf6 gxf6 17. Nd5 $18
) 14. Bg5 Nxe4 15. Qxe4 Qxe4 16. Nxg7+ Bxg7 17. Nxe4 O-O 18. Rad1 $18 {Black
will lose a pawn for insufficient compensation.} Rc6 19. Bf6 Be6 20. Bxg7 Kxg7
21. Nxd6 b5 22. cxb5 axb5 23. Nxb5 Rc5 24. Nd6 Ra8 25. b4 Rc2 26. Rxe5 Raxa2
27. Ne4 Rab2 28. b5 Re2 29. h4 h6 30. Rd4 Ba2 31. Rc5 Be6 32. Kh2 Rb3 33. Rc7
Rbb2 34. Rc3 Bf5 35. Rg3+ Kf8 36. Nf6 Rxf2 37. Ng8 Ke8 38. Nxh6 Be6 39. Rg5 f6
40. Rg7 Kf8 41. Rg3 Rxb5 42. Ng4 Rf1 43. Ne3 Rfb1 44. Rf4 R1b4 45. Rxf6+ Ke7
46. Rh6 Re4 47. Rf3 Rbe5 48. Nf1 Ra4 49. Rh7+ Kd6 50. Rd3+ Kc5 51. Nd2 Re2 52.
Nf3 Rg4 53. Rh5+ Kb6 54. Kh1 Bf7 55. Rf5 Bg6 56. Rb3+ Kc7 57. Rc5+ Kd8 58. Rb8+
Ke7 59. Rb7+ Kf8 60. Rc8+ Be8 61. Rbb8 Rg6 62. Ng5 Rh6 63. Rc4 Kg7 64. Rb7+ Kg8
65. Rg4 Rg6 66. Kh2 Bc6 67. Rc7 Be8 68. Re4 Rxe4 69. Nxe4 Re6 70. Ng5 Re2 71.
Kh3 Ra2 72. Ne4 Kf8 73. g4 Ra3+ 74. Ng3 Rd3 75. h5 Bd7 76. Rc4 Kg7 77. Kh4 Rd5
78. Rf4 Ra5 79. Rd4 Be6 80. Ne4 Bc8 81. Rc4 Be6 82. Rc7+ Kf8 83. h6 1-0

