1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nc6 4. O-O Bd7 5. Re1 a6 $2 {Even Super-GMs like
Nepo do not know everything!} 6. Bxc6 Bxc6 7. d4 cxd4 8. Nxd4 Bd7 (8... Nf6 9.
Nxc6 bxc6 10. Qf3 e5 11. Nd2 Be7 12. Nc4 O-O 13. Bg5 Ne8 14. Bd2) (8... Rc8 9.
Bg5 h6 (9... Nf6 10. Bxf6 gxf6 11. Nc3) 10. Bh4) 9. Bg5 {White chooses the
"Coffee House" strategy - playing for quick development and an attack.} (9. c4)
9... Nf6 $6 10. Bxf6 $1 gxf6 11. Nc3 $16 e6 12. Qh5 $1 Bg7 13. Rad1 $1 $16 {
This is how you must play chess! Sound positional moves until the moment of
the sacrifice!} Rc8 (13... O-O 14. Re3 $18) 14. Nf5 $3 $18 {And here is the
sacrifice!} exf5 15. exf5+ Kf8 16. Ne4 Bc6 17. Nxd6 {Black is up a piece but
his bishop on g7 and rook on h8 cannot enter the game.} Qc7 18. Nxc8 Qxc8 19.
Rd4 Qc7 20. Qd1 (20. Red1 $1 $18) 20... Bh6 21. h4 Qa5 22. Rd8+ Kg7 23. Qg4+
Bg5 24. Rdd1 h6 25. a3 Qc7 26. Qg3 Qa5 27. f4 Qc5+ 28. Re3 Bxg2 29. fxg5 hxg5
30. hxg5 Rh1+ 31. Kxg2 Qc6+ 32. Rf3 Rxd1 33. gxf6+ Kxf6 34. Qh4+ Kg7 35. f6+
Kg8 36. Qg3+ Kf8 37. Qb8+ Qe8 38. Rh3 Rd2+ 39. Kf3 1-0

