1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nc6 4. O-O Bd7 5. Re1 Nf6 6. c3 a6 7. Bf1 Bg4 8. h3
Bxf3 9. Qxf3 g6 10. d3 Bg7 11. Be3 O-O 12. Nd2 e5 {Now we cannot play d4.
Let's see how to fight this ...e5-idea:} 13. Bg5 b5 14. a4 Qe7 {How should
White continue here?} 15. Be2 $3 {Preparing Bd1-Bb3 as well as Nf1-Ne3!! This
is one of the greatest positional moves that I have ever seen!} h6 16. Bh4 $1 {
we are not in a hurry to take on f6 because g6-g5 is always bad for black} Qe6
$6 (16... Rfb8 $14) (16... g5 $2 {weakens f5.} 17. Bg3 $16) 17. Bd1 $1 Nd7 $6 (
17... Na5 $2 18. Nf1 $5 $14) 18. Bb3 $16 c4 $2 19. axb5 $1 axb5 20. dxc4 Nc5
21. cxb5 $1 $18 {Maze -Sequera Paolini, 2015 (1-0).} *

