{[%evp 0,6,16,16,56,46,85,52,69]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 {By playing 3.
..Nd7 will often continue with ... a6, with the idea of getting the pair of
bishops. The disadvantage of 3...Nd7 is ... the knight on d7! It's placed less
active compared to a knight on c6. White has two main plans: 1) Continuing
with 4.d4 cxd4 5.Qxd4 2) Playing c3-d4 There are also less common moves like 4.
Ba4 or 4.a4, which have become quite fashionable. Before going into the
specific theory (in the following two lectures), we will examine typical ideas
and plans.} *

