1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. c3 (4. O-O a6 5. Ba4 b5 6. Bb3 c4) 4... Ngf6
5. Qe2 $1 ({A horrible move would be} 5. e5 {- this may work with a knight on
c6, but not here.} dxe5 6. Nxe5 a6 7. Bxd7+ (7. Nxd7 Bxd7 8. Bxd7+ Qxd7) 7...
Nxd7 8. Nxd7 Bxd7 9. O-O Bc6 {Black is already strategically winning.}) (5. Bd3
$5) 5... Qc7 6. O-O ({We cannot play} 6. d4 {yet:} cxd4 7. cxd4 $4 Qxc1+ $19)
6... e6 $6 {Black sould have played the move ...a6 earlier !} 7. d4 {with a
very nice advantage} Be7 ({Now} 7... a6 {can be met with} 8. Bd3 $1 $16) 8. Bg5
$5 {Unusual, but playable.} (8. Nbd2 {would be the standard continuation. For
example} O-O 9. Re1 a6 10. Bd3 (10. Ba4 b5 11. Bc2 (11. Bb3) 11... cxd4 12.
Nxd4) 10... b5 11. Nf1 Bb7 (11... c4 $6 12. Bc2 Bb7 13. Ng3 $16) 12. Ng3 cxd4
13. cxd4 e5 14. d5 (14. Nf5 Rfe8 15. d5 $16) 14... Nc5 15. Bc2 Rac8 16. Bd2 Qb8
17. Rac1 $16) (8. e5 $5 dxe5 9. dxe5 Nd5 10. c4 N5b6 11. Nc3 $16) 8... e5 {
How should White continue?} (8... O-O 9. Nbd2) 9. dxe5 $1 dxe5 10. c4 $3 {
[%csl Gd5][%cal Yb1c3,Yc3d5] A great example of how to handle such positions!
White played the opening at the level of a good GM!} O-O 11. Bxd7 $3 (11. Nc3
Nb6) (11. h3 Nb8 (11... Nb6) 12. Ba4 a6 13. Bc2) (11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. Nc3 Bg4 13.
Nd5 Nxd5 14. exd5 Bd6 15. Ba4 f5) 11... Bxd7 12. Nc3 Rfe8 (12... Bc6 13. Bxf6
$1 {Before White can move this knight, White takes it and leaves Black with
inactive bishops - just like it happened in the game!} Bxf6 14. Rad1 $16 (14.
Nd5 Bxd5 15. cxd5)) 13. Bxf6 $1 Bxf6 14. Nd5 Qc6 15. Rad1 $16 Rad8 (15... b6
16. Nxf6+ gxf6 17. Nh4 $18) 16. Qe3 (16. Rd2 Be6 17. Rfd1) 16... Be6 17. b3 (
17. Nxf6+ gxf6 18. Rd5 Bxd5 19. cxd5 Qc7 20. Nh4 Kh8 21. Nf5 Rg8 22. d6 (22. h4
) 22... Rxd6 23. Nxd6 Qxd6) 17... Bxd5 18. exd5 Qd6 19. Nd2 (19. Rfe1 e4 20.
Nd2 Bd4) (19. Qe4 g6 {How should White fight against the plan ...Bg7, ...f5,
etc.?} 20. Rfe1 (20. g4 $5) 20... Bg7 21. g4 $1 $16 {Forced, but strong. For
example} Rf8 22. g5 $1 {White continues to figth against ...f5.} f5 23. gxf6
Rxf6 (23... Qxf6 24. Kg2) 24. Ng5 $1 $16 {[%cal Yg5e6]} (24. Nxe5 $2 Re8 $132))
19... b6 20. Rfe1 Re7 $16 21. Qg3 Kh8 22. Ne4 Qd7 23. Qf3 Bh4 24. g3 Qh3 25.
Qh5 f5 26. Ng5 1-0

