1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. O-O Ngf6 5. Re1 a6 6. Bf1 b6 7. d3 {This is
a bit passive.} (7. d4 $1 {is best according to theory. After} cxd4 8. Nxd4 Bb7
9. f3 e6 10. c4 Be7 11. Nc3 O-O 12. Be3 $14 {we get a typical Hedgehog
position.}) 7... Bb7 8. Nc3 g6 {Since White played the slow d3, Black has time
for ...g6, ...Bg7.} 9. Ne2 Bg7 10. Ng3 O-O 11. c3 {How should Black continue
in this position?} Qc7 $2 ({After} 11... e5 $1 $15 {Black is better. The
f1-bishop is restricted and White doesn't have a constructive plan. For example
} 12. d4 (12. h3 Re8 13. Bd2 d5 14. exd5 Nxd5 15. Ne4 Qc7 $17) 12... exd4 13.
cxd4 cxd4 14. Nxd4 Re8 $17) 12. d4 e5 13. d5 {This is best under the
circumstances. Black's b7-bishop is misplaced in this structure.} ({Usually,
we take on e5 in such positions. Here, however, our knight is already on g3.
So, after taking on e5, Black stands very well, since this knight is misplaced.
} 13. dxe5 Nxe5 14. Nxe5 dxe5 15. f3 c4 16. Be3 b5 $15) 13... c4 14. Bg5 b5
$132 15. Qd2 Rfc8 ({Black should play} 15... Nc5 $1 {and reroute the bishop
with ...Bc8-Bd7.} 16. Bh6 Bc8 17. Bxg7 Kxg7 18. Qg5 Qd8 (18... Qe7 $2 19. Nh5+
$1 $18) 19. h3 h6 20. Qd2 Bd7 $15) 16. Rab1 Nc5 17. b3 cxb3 18. axb3 Qb6 19. h3
Rcb8 20. b4 Na4 21. c4 bxc4 22. Bxc4 Bc8 23. Rec1 a5 24. Be3 Qb7 25. b5 Nd7 26.
Ra1 Nac5 27. Rxa5 Qc7 28. Rxa8 Rxa8 29. Be2 Qd8 30. Rb1 Qf8 31. Ne1 f5 32. exf5
gxf5 33. f4 Bh6 34. Nf3 Ra3 35. Bxc5 Nxc5 36. Nh5 Bb7 37. Ng5 exf4 38. h4 Re3
39. Nxf4 Qe7 40. Nfe6 Re5 41. Bc4 Qf6 42. Nxc5 dxc5 43. d6+ Kg7 44. d7 Qd8 45.
Qd6 Bxg5 46. hxg5 Re4 47. Qf6+ 1-0

