{A good game by White in the "Spanish" positions of the Moscow Sicilian!} 1. e4
c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. c3 Ngf6 5. Qe2 a6 6. Ba4 b5 7. Bc2 Bb7 8. d4 e5 9.
d5 {Even though Black manages to get a setup with ...g6-Bg7, d4-d5 is a good
move since the b7-bishop will be misplaced.} c4 {This is premature - ...c5-c4
works if a4 is already on the board.} (9... g6 $1 10. O-O Bg7 11. a4 c4 12. Be3
$3 O-O 13. Na3 $1) 10. b3 $3 $16 Rc8 (10... cxb3 11. axb3 Rc8 12. O-O Be7 13.
Bd2 $1 O-O 14. Na3 $1 Qb6 (14... Re8 15. c4 $3 $16) 15. b4 $3 (15. c4 b4 $1)
15... Qc7 16. Bb3 $1 Nb6 17. Rfc1 $3 Qd7 18. h3 $1 (18. c4 Qg4 $5) 18... Bd8
19. c4 bxc4 20. Nxc4 Qb5 21. Be3 $16) 11. O-O Be7 12. b4 $5 (12. bxc4 $1 Rxc4
13. a4 $16) 12... a5 $6 (12... O-O) 13. a4 $3 axb4 14. cxb4 bxa4 15. Nc3 O-O
16. Rxa4 $16 {White has a big advantage due to her advantage in space and the
misplaced bishop on b7.} Ra8 17. Be3 Rxa4 18. Bxa4 Qa8 19. Ra1 Rc8 20. Ra2 Qb8
21. Nb5 Ba6 22. Na7 Rc7 23. b5 Bc8 24. Nc6 Rxc6 25. dxc6 Nb6 26. Bc2 h6 27.
Bxb6 Qxb6 28. Ra8 Qc7 29. Qxc4 Kh7 30. b6 Qxb6 31. Rxc8 Ng4 32. Qe2 Qb2 33. h3
Nf6 34. c7 Qb7 35. Rb8 Qxc7 36. Rb1 Nd7 37. Bb3 Nc5 38. Bxf7 Qa5 39. Qb5 Qc3
40. Qe8 {An amazing game by Kosteniuk!} 1-0

