{A great and very instructive game in the Moscow Variation with 4.d4:} 1. e4 c5
2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. d4 (4. O-O {is another possible move order.} a6 5.
Bxd7+ Bxd7 6. d4 cxd4 7. Qxd4) 4... cxd4 (4... a6 5. Bxd7+ Bxd7 6. dxc5 $1 dxc5
7. Nc3 $14) 5. Qxd4 a6 6. Bxd7+ Bxd7 7. Nc3 e5 (7... h6 8. O-O e5 (8... Nf6 9.
e5 dxe5 10. Nxe5 $14) 9. Qd3) (7... Nf6 8. Bg5 $14) (7... e6 8. Bg5 $14) 8. Qd3
Rc8 (8... Nf6 9. Bg5 Be6 10. O-O Be7 11. Bxf6 (11. Rfd1) 11... Bxf6 12. Rfd1
Be7 13. Nd5 Bxd5 14. Qxd5 Qc7 15. c3 O-O {Now, we want to transfer our knight
to d5:} 16. Ne1 Rac8 17. Nc2 {From here, the knight has two ways to reach d5 -
via e3 and via b4.} Rfd8 18. Qd3 Bg5 19. Nb4 g6 20. Nd5 $16) 9. O-O (9. Bg5 $5
Qc7 $1 (9... Be7 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. Rd1 $14) 10. O-O h6 $1 11. Bh4 (11. Be3 Nf6
$15) 11... g5 $1 12. Bg3 Nf6 $132) 9... h6 $1 ({After} 9... Nf6 $2 {White is
very happy to pin the knight with} 10. Bg5 {, leading to an advantage for
White.} Be6 11. Rfd1 Be7 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. Qxd6 $16) 10. Nd2 {For some time,
Black scored very well from this position. This was mainly due to playing the
pointless move 10.Be3? With Nd2, White prepares to transfer the knight to e3
via c4 or f1.} (10. Be3 $2 Nf6 11. a4 Be7 12. Rfd1 O-O 13. a5 Be6 14. Bb6 Qd7
15. h3 Qc6 {Black has a very good game since White finds it hard to come up
with a constructive plan.}) 10... Be6 (10... b5 11. a4 $1 b4 12. Nd5 $16) 11.
Rd1 Nf6 12. Nf1 (12. a4 d5 $1 $132) 12... Be7 13. Ne3 O-O 14. Bd2 (14. a4 $1)
14... Re8 $2 (14... b5 15. a4 Qb6 $132) 15. Be1 (15. a4) 15... Bf8 $2 {A very
passive move, giving up on all the active ideas with ...Nh5-Bg5.} (15... Nh5
16. Ned5 Nf4 $1 $132) 16. a4 $1 Qc7 17. f3 $14 Nh5 18. Kh1 $1 (18. a5 Nf4 19.
Qd2 $14) (18. Bg3 $2) (18. g3) 18... Qc6 (18... Nf4 19. Qd2) 19. Qd2 (19. a5 $1
Nf4 20. Qd2 Red8 21. Bh4 g5 22. Bg3 Nh5 23. Bf2 Nf4 24. Ncd5 (24. Rac1 $1 Qc7
25. Ned5 $3 (25. Ncd5 Bxd5 26. Nxd5 Nxd5 27. Qxd5 Qc6 28. c4 Qxd5 29. exd5 $3 (
29. Rxd5) 29... f5 30. b4) 25... Nxd5 26. exd5 Bf5 27. Bb6) 24... Bxd5 (24...
Nxd5 25. exd5) 25. exd5 $1 Qd7 26. g4) 19... Nf4 20. Bg3 $14 Qb6 (20... Nh5 21.
Bf2 Nf4 22. a5 Red8 23. Bg3 $1 (23. Na4 d5) 23... Nh5 24. Bh4 Re8 25. Na4 $1
$16 Nf4 26. Nb6 Rb8 27. c4 $1 $16 g5 28. Bg3 (28. Bf2) 28... Nh5 29. Bf2 Nf4
30. b4) 21. Rab1 Nh5 22. Ncd5 Qc6 23. a5 g6 (23... Nxg3+ 24. hxg3 Red8 25. c4
Bxd5 26. Qxd5 Qxd5 27. Rxd5 g6 28. g4) 24. Bh4 Kh8 25. c3 $16 f5 26. exf5 gxf5
27. Qc2 Bxd5 (27... f4 28. Nf6 Nxf6 (28... fxe3 29. Qh7#) 29. Bxf6+ Bg7 30. Qg6
) 28. Nxd5 e4 29. Qd2 $1 Re6 (29... exf3 30. gxf3) 30. Rf1 Qe8 31. fxe4 fxe4
32. Rbe1 Qg6 33. h3 Ng3+ 34. Bxg3 Qxg3 35. Re3 Qg5 36. g4 Re5 37. Nb6 Rd8 38.
c4 Bg7 39. Qe2 Rxa5 40. Nd5 Ra2 41. Rb3 b5 42. Nf4 bxc4 43. Rb7 Re8 44. Qxc4
Rxb2 45. Qf7 Rf8 46. Qxf8+ Bxf8 47. Ng6+ Qxg6 48. Rxf8+ Qg8 49. Rxg8+ Kxg8 50.
Rxb2 1-0

