1. e4 $5 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. d4 cxd4 5. Qxd4 a6 6. Bxd7+ Bxd7 7. c4 (7.
Nc3 e5 8. Qd3) 7... b5 8. Nc3 e5 9. Qd3 bxc4 10. Qxc4 Qc8 (10... h6 11. Nd5 Rc8
12. Qxa6 Nf6 13. Nxf6+ Qxf6 14. O-O $13) 11. Qd3 (11. Qxc8+ Rxc8 12. O-O f5
$132) 11... h6 12. O-O Nf6 13. Nd2 Be6 14. Rd1 Be7 15. Nf1 Qb7 $1 16. Ne3 Rc8
$1 {I rejected castling since I anticipated the coming endgame!} ({After} 16...
O-O 17. Ned5 Bxd5 18. Nxd5 Nxd5 19. Qxd5 Qxd5 20. Rxd5 Rfc8 21. Bd2 $11 {
the Kg8 is far from the action!}) 17. Ned5 Nxd5 18. Nxd5 (18. exd5 $2 Bg4 $3
19. Re1 Bh5 $17) 18... Bxd5 19. Qxd5 Qxd5 20. Rxd5 Kd7 $1 {The king finds an
excellent position on e6.} 21. Bd2 Ke6 22. Ra5 Rc6 23. Kf1 (23. Bc3 $6 Bd8 24.
Ra4 Bb6 $1 25. Kf1 Ra8 26. Ke2 f5 $15 (26... g6 $15)) 23... Rb8 (23... Rhc8 $5
24. Bc3 Bd8 $15 25. Ra4 f5) 24. Rc1 $1 {It's in White's favor to exchange a
rook. I forgot about Rc1, only seeing it after having played 23...Rb8?!} (24.
Bc3 h5 (24... Bd8) 25. Ke2 g6 26. Rd1 f5 27. f3 Rg8 $15 (27... Rf8)) 24...
Rxc1+ 25. Bxc1 Rb6 26. Ke2 Rc6 27. Be3 Rc2+ 28. Kd3 Rxb2 29. Rxa6 f5 $5 (29...
Bg5 30. a4 Bxe3 31. Kxe3 Rb3+ 32. Ke2 g6 33. a5 $11) 30. a4 $6 fxe4+ 31. Kxe4
