1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. c3 Ngf6 {After virtually any other move, we
can play d4. For example:} (4... e6 5. d4 a6 6. Bd3) (4... g6 5. d4) (4... Qc7
5. d4 a6 6. Bd3) 5. Bd3 a6 6. Bc2 b5 7. d4 Bb7 8. Nbd2 e6 9. O-O Be7 10. Re1 e5
$6 {Going for the Spanish after all. However, Black lost a tempo playing ...e6
and ...e5 in two moves.} 11. Nf1 {Here d5 would have been quite strong, but
keeping the tension is also fine.} (11. d5 $1 $16 {[%csl Rb7]}) 11... Qc7 ({
If, for example} 11... O-O {the game can continue with} 12. Ng3 g6 13. Bh6 Re8
14. h3 Bf8 ({Again, the capture on d4 benefits White:} 14... cxd4 15. cxd4 Rc8
16. Bb3 $16 {The bishop can switch to a great diagonal and Black no longer has
...c4.}) 15. Bg5 $16 (15. Qd2)) 12. Ng3 g6 13. Bh6 $16 Bf8 14. Bxf8 (14. Qd2 $5
) 14... Nxf8 15. a4 {White is striking on the queenside since Black is lagging
with his development.} Ne6 16. d5 Nf4 17. Ne2 N4h5 18. h3 Qd7 19. Qd2 h6 20.
axb5 axb5 21. Rxa8+ Bxa8 22. Ra1 Bb7 23. c4 g5 24. b4 O-O 25. bxc5 dxc5 26.
cxb5 Qd6 27. Qc3 Re8 28. Nd2 Nd7 29. Nc4 Qf6 30. Ra7 Rb8 31. Qa5 Nf4 32. Ng3 g4
33. hxg4 Qg6 34. Bd1 Bxd5 35. exd5 Qd3 36. Ne3 Nb6 37. Bc2 Qd4 38. Qxb6 Rxb6
39. Ra8+ Kg7 40. Nef5+ Kf6 41. Nxd4 exd4 42. Ra6 Nxd5 43. Rxb6+ Nxb6 44. Ne4+
1-0

