1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. c3 Ngf6 5. Bd3 a6 6. a4 (6. Bc2 b5 7. d4 Bb7
8. Nbd2 e6 9. O-O) 6... b6 {How do we continue - Bc2 or 0-0?} 7. O-O ({After} 
7. Bc2 Bb7 {our e4-pawn is attacked and we are not ready to play Re1 yet.})
7... Bb7 8. Qe2 ({I prefer} 8. Re1 {, for example} Qc7 9. Na3 e6 10. Bc2 Be7
11. d4 O-O 12. Bd3 $14 (12. d5 $5)) 8... Qc7 9. Na3 e6 10. Bc2 Be7 11. d4 O-O
12. Bf4 Rfc8 (12... Nh5 {We just return the bishop when the knight has no
business on h5.} 13. Bd2 g6 14. Rfe1 Rfe8 15. Bd3 (15. h3) 15... Nhf6 16. h3 d5
17. e5 Ne4 18. Bh6 Qd8 {Now, I like} 19. Nb1 $5 {, rerouting the knight to
better squares.} (19. Nd2 {is a second possibility.}) 19... cxd4 20. cxd4 Bb4 (
20... a5 21. Nbd2 Nxd2 22. Qxd2 Bf8 23. Bb5 $1 $18) 21. Nbd2 Qe7 22. Rec1 Nxd2
23. Nxd2 $16) 13. Bd3 Nh5 $6 14. Bd2 $14 Nhf6 15. Rfe1 cxd4 16. cxd4 d5 $6 17.
e5 $16 Ne4 18. h4 h6 19. Nc2 f5 20. exf6 Bxf6 21. Ne3 h5 $2 {Creating too many
weaknesses.} 22. Nf1 Qd6 23. Be3 Rf8 24. Ng5 $18 g6 25. Bxe4 dxe4 26. Ng3 Qd5
27. N3xe4 Bxg5 28. Bxg5 Qxd4 29. Rad1 Qxe4 30. Qxe4 Bxe4 31. Rxe4 Nc5 32. Rc4
Rfc8 33. Be3 Kf7 34. a5 Ke8 35. axb6 Nb7 36. Rc7 Rxc7 37. bxc7 Rc8 38. Bb6 Ke7
39. b4 e5 40. Kf1 Rf8 41. Ke2 Rc8 42. Ke3 Ke6 43. Rd8 Nd6 44. Kd3 e4+ 45. Kd4
Nf5+ 46. Kxe4 Nd6+ 47. Kf4 Ke7 48. Kg5 Ke6 49. Kxg6 Ke7 50. f4 Ke6 51. f5+ Ke7
52. f6+ Ke6 53. f7 Nxf7 54. Rxc8 Ne5+ 55. Kg7 Nd7 56. Re8+ Kf5 57. c8=Q Kg4 58.
Qxd7+ Kg3 59. Qh3+ Kf4 60. Qf3# 1-0

