{[%evp 0,27,16,16,33,45,70,31,31,35,41,42,38,31,26,4,13,13,30,30,22,30,29,29,
22,22,17,21,16,12]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 {I have no doubt that this
is objectively the best answer to 3.Bb5+. However, I do not recommend it from
Black's perspective because it offers very few winning chances. Before going
into the theory in Lesson 7, we discuss White's general plans after} 4. Bxd7+
Qxd7 {, Black's best move, and the also quite common} (4... Nxd7 5. O-O Ngf6 6.
Qe2 {Here we will see several possible plans. The most popular one is going
for a Hedgehog setup with d4 and c4.}) 5. O-O Nf6 6. Re1 Nc6 7. c3 e6 8. d4
cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 10. e5 Ne4 11. Nbd2 Nxd2 12. Bxd2 Be7 {Here, White can choose
between more positional plans with h4 and attacking plans with Rc1-Rc1, etc.}
13. Rc1 (13. h4) 13... O-O 14. Rc3 *

