1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Nxd7 5. O-O Ngf6 6. Qe2 e6 7. b3 {
Another clever plan - White can later go for the hedgehog and will later play
c4 and d4.} ({White can also start with} 7. d4 cxd4 8. Nxd4 Rc8 9. c4 a6 10. b3
{The best move order.} ({After} 10. Nc3 Be7 11. b3 {Black can play} b5 {
since our knight is hanging.}) 10... Be7 11. Bb2 O-O 12. Nc3 {White can play
on the queenside or on the kingside - f4, etc.}) 7... Be7 8. Bb2 O-O 9. a4 (9.
d4) ({or} 9. c4 {with the idea d4.} {If} e5 10. Nc3 {Black is statically worse.
}) 9... Qc7 10. d3 b6 11. Nfd2 $5 {White chooses a strategy, similar to the
one with d3-Ng5.} a6 ({Perhaps Black should improved the position of this
knight with} 11... Nb8 12. f4 Nc6) 12. f4 b5 (12... Nb8 13. g4 $1 {Very
powerful - White attacks on the kingside.} (13. Nc3 {is too slow because of}
Nc6 14. Nd1 Nd4) 13... Nc6 14. g5 Nd7 15. Qg2 Nd4 (15... b5 16. f5 (16. Nc3 b4
(16... Nd4 17. Nf3) 17. Nd1 Nd4 18. Ne3 $18)) 16. Nf3 Nxf3+ 17. Rxf3 b5 18. f5
$1 $16 (18. Nd2)) 13. Nc3 Rab8 (13... b4 $2 14. Nd1 d5 15. Ne3 {Black can
never push ...c4 and remains without counterplay.} Nb8 16. g4 Nc6 17. g5 Nd7
18. Qg2 dxe4 19. dxe4 $16 (19. Nxe4 $16)) 14. Kh1 d5 $6 15. axb5 (15. exd5 $1
b4 16. d6 $1 Bxd6 17. Nce4 $16) 15... axb5 16. exd5 b4 17. Nd1 (17. d6 $1 Bxd6
18. Nce4 $14) 17... Nxd5 18. f5 exf5 19. Rxf5 $13 N7f6 20. Ne3 $2 (20. Qf3 $14)
20... Nf4 $2 (20... Nxe3 21. Qxe3 Qxh2+ $1 22. Kxh2 Ng4+ 23. Kh3 Nxe3 $19) 21.
Qf3 Ng6 22. Bxf6 Bxf6 23. Nd5 $18 Qd6 24. Ne4 Qe6 25. Ndxf6+ gxf6 26. Rf1 1-0

