Bb2 O-O 9. c4 {In this game we see the plan with c4-d4, leading to the
Hedgehog structure.} a6 10. d4 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Rc8 12. Nc3 Qa5 13. Rad1 Rfd8 14.
Kh1 (14. Rd3 $5) 14... Qh5 15. Qxh5 {I would rather keep the queens on the
board. White keeps a small advantage after the exchange of queens.} Nxh5 16. f4
Nc5 17. g3 Nf6 18. Rfe1 Bf8 19. Kg2 $14 {The king should come to the centre in
the endgame.} d5 $6 20. cxd5 exd5 21. e5 $1 Nfe4 22. Nde2 (22. Re3 $1) 22...
Nxc3 23. Nxc3 (23. Bxc3 $1 $14) 23... d4 $132 24. Ne2 Ne6 $2 (24... d3 $1) 25.
