{A perfect exmple for White in the hedgehog setup after 4...Nxd7. I trust that
you study this game particularly well to figure out the typical plans!} 1. e4
c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Nxd7 5. O-O Ngf6 (5... e6 {What are good
options for White after this?} 6. Qe2 {A flexible move, which is useful for
any plan. Either the hedghog, the plan with Ng5-f4, and c3-d4.} (6. d4 cxd4 7.
Qxd4 (7. Nxd4)) 6... Be7 {And now? We can choose between the plans we are
already familiar with:} (6... g6 7. c3) 7. d4 (7. d3 Ngf6 (7... h6 8. d4 $5 {
We can switch plans - the extra move ...h6 is hardly to Black's advantage.} (8.
Nfd2 $5 {[%cal Yf2f4]}) (8. c3 $5 {[%cal Yd3d4]}) 8... cxd4 9. Nxd4 a6 10. c4
Ngf6 11. Nc3 O-O 12. b3 Rc8 13. Bb2 $14) (7... e5 8. c3 $1 Ngf6 9. d4 $14) (
7... g5 {is asking way to much. Black cannot play like this with his king
still in the centre.} 8. c3 g4 9. Nfd2 h5 10. f4 $16 (10. d4 $5)) 8. a4 (8. Ng5
)) (7. c3 {is another possible plan.}) 7... cxd4 8. Nxd4 Qb6 (8... a6 9. c4) 9.
Nf3 Ngf6 10. c4 O-O 11. Nc3 Qc6 12. b3 a6 13. Bb2 $14 {A nice hedgehog
position for White, with a tough battle ahead.}) 6. Qe2 e6 7. d4 cxd4 8. Nxd4
Be7 9. c4 O-O 10. Nc3 Rc8 11. b3 a6 12. Bb2 $14 Qa5 13. Kh1 Rfe8 14. f4 Bf8 15.
Nf3 $5 ({According to the computer} 15. g4 $3 {is very powerful. Can White
really play like this in the Hedgehog? It's possible due to the absence of
light-squared bishops. With a bishop on b7, g4 would be difficult to achieve.}
e5 (15... g6 16. e5 $1 (16. g5 Nh5 17. Rad1) 16... dxe5 17. fxe5 Qxe5 18. Qxe5
Nxe5 19. Rxf6 Nd3 20. Rb1 Bg7 21. Ne4 $1 $16) 16. fxe5 {If Black takes with
the knight} Nxe5 (16... dxe5 17. Nf5 $16) {we should not hesitate to play} 17.
Rxf6 $1 gxf6 18. Nd5 Bg7 19. Nf5 $18) 15... e5 (15... h6 16. e5 dxe5 17. fxe5
Nh7 18. Ne4 $16) 16. f5 b5 {It is vital for Black to create counterplay.} 17.
Nd2 $1 $14 {White has to defend c4.} (17. g4 $2 bxc4 18. g5 Nh5 $17) 17... b4
$4 {Black is blocking his own play! The Abdusattorov of today would have
played much better.} 18. Nd1 $16 Nc5 19. g4 Nfd7 20. g5 $18 Qd8 21. Rg1 Nb8 22.
Ne3 Nc6 23. Nd5 a5 24. g6 fxg6 25. fxg6 Ne6 26. gxh7+ Kh8 27. Qg4 Ncd4 28. Raf1
Rb8 29. Bxd4 exd4 (29... Nxd4 $2 30. Rxf8+ Rxf8 31. Qxg7#) 30. Nf3 $18 Rb7 31.
Nh4 g5 32. Ng6+ Kxh7 33. Qh5+ Bh6 34. Nf6+ Kg7 35. Ng4 Rh8 36. Nxh8 Qxh8 37.
Rf6 Qh7 38. Rxe6 1-0

