1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Nxd7 5. O-O Ngf6 6. Qe2 Rc8 {Again,
this clever move, aimed at stopping c4.} 7. c3 (7. d3 {White could have
adjusted and gone for the plan with d3. What do we play against ...e5, ...g6,
and ...e6?} e6 (7... g6 8. c3) (7... e5 8. c3) 8. Ng5 {This looks quite clever
now.} (8. Nfd2) 8... h6 9. Nh3 Be7 10. f4 O-O 11. c4 {Now, both ...d5 and ...
b5 can be met with Nc3.} (11. g4) 11... b5 (11... d5 12. Nc3 $14 {Now we would
like to see} d4 13. Nd1 {when after the centre is closed, we have a free hand
on the kingside.}) 12. Nc3 $14 {We are not afraid of} bxc4 13. dxc4) 7... e6 8.
d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 10. e5 Ne4 11. Be3 h6 12. Ne1 $5 {A new plan - not
exchanging the e4-knight but pushing it back with f3.} Be7 13. f3 Ng5 14. Nd3
O-O 15. Nc3 $14 {White is better since the g5-knight is misplaced.} Nb6 16.
Rac1 Nc4 17. Bf2 Qd7 18. f4 Nh7 19. b3 Nb6 20. Nc5 Bxc5 21. dxc5 Na8 22. Bd4
Nc7 23. b4 f5 24. b5 g5 25. g3 Rf7 26. Kh1 Rg7 27. a4 Kh8 28. Nd1 Ne8 29. Ne3
Qf7 30. g4 gxf4 31. Rxf4 Ng5 32. gxf5 Ne4 33. f6 Rg5 34. Rg1 Nc7 35. Rxg5 hxg5
36. Rf1 Rg8 37. Ng4 Rg6 38. Rf3 Kg8 39. Kg2 b6 40. cxb6 axb6 41. Rh3 Ne8 42.
Nh6+ Rxh6 43. Rxh6 Qc7 44. Rg6+ Kf7 45. Rh6 1-0

