1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Qxd7 {Against this we have to adjust
our plans. Black will develop his knight to c6 where it's placed much more
actively.} 5. O-O Nf6 6. Re1 Nc6 7. c3 g6 $2 {A mistake that you are bound to
face!} 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 Bg7 (9... e6 10. e5 (10. d5 exd5 11. exd5+ Ne7 12.
Nc3 Bg7 13. Qe2 O-O (13... Kf8 14. Bg5 (14. Qd3) 14... Nfxd5 15. Nxd5 Nxd5 16.
Rad1) 14. Qxe7 Rfe8 15. Qxd7 Rxe1+ 16. Nxe1 Nxd7) 10... dxe5 11. dxe5 Qxd1 12.
Rxd1 Nd5) 10. Nc3 O-O 11. d5 $1 ({We can use the same idea after} 11. Bg5 Rac8
12. Rc1 Rfd8 13. d5 Na5 14. b3 $1 $16 {, but here we cannot get it by force.}
h6 (14... Rxc3 $2 15. Rxc3 Nxe4 16. Rc2 $18) 15. Bd2 b6 16. h3 Nb7 17. b4 a5
18. a3 $16) 11... Na5 (11... Ne5 12. Nxe5 dxe5 $14 {After this, White has a
stable advantage. For example} 13. f3 (13. h3) (13. Bg5 e6 (13... h6 14. Bh4
$14) (13... Qg4 $2 14. Qxg4 Nxg4 15. Bxe7 Rfe8 16. d6 $18 (16. Ba3) (16. Bg5))
14. dxe6 Qxe6 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. Nd5 $14) 13... e6 (13... Rac8 14. Be3 a6 15.
Qb3 $16) 14. Bg5 exd5 (14... h6 15. Bh4 $14) 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. Nxd5 $14 Bd8 $4
17. Nf6+ $18) 12. b3 $3 {An amazing move, restricting Black's knight. The
tactics work for White:} Rac8 (12... Nxe4 {is not possible due} 13. Nxe4 Bxa1
14. Bd2 $18 {with a double attack.}) 13. Bd2 {[%csl Ra5] This position is
strategically lost due to the unfortunate position of the a5-knight.} b6 14.
Rc1 Nb7 (14... h6 15. Qe2 Rfe8 16. Qd3 Ng4 17. h3 Ne5 18. Nxe5 Bxe5 19. Bxh6
$18 (19. Qe2 Nb7 20. b4 $16)) 15. b4 (15. e5) 15... a5 16. a3 $16 *

