1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Qxd7 5. O-O {Here we going to look at
the plans with an early ...g6 and ...e5 - as a rule they do not work.} Nf6 (
5... g6 $2 6. c3 $1 $16 Nf6 7. Qe2 Bg7 8. d4 O-O {White is better in various
ways, for example} 9. Rd1 $14 (9. dxc5) (9. h3)) 6. Re1 e5 $2 7. c3 Nc6 8. d4
Be7 9. Bg5 ({The strategy which was good after ...Nxd7 does not work here} 9.
dxc5 dxc5 10. c4 $2 Bd6 11. Nc3 Nd4 {since Black's knight can go to d4.}) 9...
Qc7 10. dxe5 dxe5 ({If} 10... Nxe5 11. Nxe5 dxe5 {then we can return to which
plan?} 12. Bxf6 (12. c4 $1 Nd7 $6 13. Bxe7 Kxe7 14. Nc3 $16) 12... Bxf6 13. c4
$16) 11. Qe2 O-O 12. a4 $14 {[%cal Yb1a3]} *

