1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Qxd7 5. O-O Nc6 6. Re1 Nf6 7. c3 e6 8.
d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 10. e5 Ne4 11. a3 $5 Be7 12. Nbd2 Nxd2 13. Bxd2 O-O 14. Rc1
Rfc8 15. h4 {The strategic way of playing.} (15. Rc3 $5) 15... Bd8 {This is
mainly played with the idea of transferring the c6-knight to the kingside via
e7.} 16. h5 h6 17. Rc3 Ne7 18. Rd3 Qc6 19. g4 {White allows ...Qc2, when in
the ensueing endgame White has some advantage due to his advantage in space.
However, Vachier Lagrave defended extremely well and managed to draw.} Qc2 $1 {
A brave decision - Black saw that he can save his rook on c2.} 20. Qxc2 Rxc2
21. Bc3 $14 Nc6 22. Red1 Bg5 $1 {The saving resource after which White remains
with a small positional advantage.} 23. Ne1 Rc1 24. Rxc1 Bxc1 25. Rd1 Bg5 26.
Nd3 Bd8 27. Nc5 b6 28. Nd3 b5 29. Nb4 Na5 30. Na6 Nb3 31. Nc5 Nxc5 32. dxc5 Kf8
33. b4 Ke8 34. a4 bxa4 35. Ra1 Kd7 36. Rxa4 Kc6 37. Ra6+ Kb5 38. Rd6 a5 39.
bxa5 Bxa5 40. Bxa5 Rxa5 41. Rd7 Kxc5 42. Rxf7 d4 43. Rxg7 d3 44. Rd7 Kc4 45. f4
Rd5 1/2-1/2

