1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Qxd7 5. O-O Nf6 6. Re1 Nc6 7. c3 e6 8.
d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 10. e5 Ne4 11. Nbd2 Nxd2 12. Bxd2 Be7 13. Rc1 O-O 14. a3
Rfc8 ({A horrible move would be} 14... g6 {Now, playing Rc3 would no longer
make sense but White gets a big advantage after} 15. Bh6 $16 {due to the
weaknesses created by ...g6.} ({or} 15. h4 $16)) 15. Rc3 Qd8 16. Rd3 Rc7 17. h4
(17. h3 Rac8 18. Nh2) 17... h6 ({If Black accepts the sacrifice with} 17...
Bxh4 18. Nxh4 Qxh4 19. Ree3 Qd8 (19... Nxd4 $2 20. g3 $18) 20. Rh3 {he would
face a huge attack.}) 18. Nh2 (18. h5 $2 {Does not fit with the previous moves
- now White's queen can no longer use h5.}) 18... Kh8 19. Qg4 Qg8 20. Rf3 Bf8
21. Nf1 Qh7 $5 {Black found an original defensive setup.} 22. Ng3 a5 23. Nh5 b5
(23... Qc2) 24. Rc1 Rac8 $2 (24... Raa7 $1 $13) 25. Rxc6 $1 Rxc6 26. Rxf7 $16 {
White has more than enough compensation for the sacrificed exchange.} Qg8 27.
Qg6 (27. Rb7 $1 $16) 27... R8c7 (27... Qh7 28. Qg4) 28. Rf3 b4 29. axb4 axb4
30. Nf4 Rf7 31. Qd3 Rxf4 32. Rxf4 Rc8 33. Qg6 b3 34. Rf7 Ra8 35. Rb7 Qh7 36. h5
Qxg6 37. hxg6 Kg8 38. Rxb3 Ra4 39. Bc3 Ra8 40. Rb6 Be7 41. Rxe6 Kf8 42. f4 1-0

