1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Qxd7 5. O-O Nc6 ({Instead of the best
continuation your are likely to face something like} 5... Nf6 6. Re1 g6 7. c3
Bg7 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 Nc6 10. Nc3 O-O {when we already know the best line:}
11. d5 $1 Na5 12. b3 $1 Rac8 13. Bd2 $16 {[%csl Ra5]}) 6. Re1 Nf6 7. c3 e6 8.
d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 10. e5 Ne4 11. Nbd2 Nxd2 12. Bxd2 Be7 ({Being a strong
positional player, Luke McShane wouldn't mind to play the position after} 12...
Bb4 13. Rc1 (13. Re3)) 13. Rc1 O-O 14. Rc3 Rfc8 (14... f6 $6 15. exf6 Bxf6 16.
Rd3 $14 (16. Bf4 $14) (16. Bg5 $14)) 15. a3 b5 16. Rd3 b4 ({Black can defend
against White's attack with} 16... f5 17. exf6 Bxf6 {but combined with ...b5
it would leave Black with too many weaknesses.} 18. Bg5 Qf7 19. Bxf6 Qxf6 20.
Rc3 $16 (20. h3)) 17. a4 {Not strictly necessary.} ({The direct} 17. Ng5 {
is possible.}) 17... h6 18. h4 Kh8 ({If} 18... Na5 {then} 19. b3 {preventing ..
.N4.}) 19. Nh2 Qe8 (19... f5 20. exf6 Bxf6 21. Qg4 Re8 22. Nf3 $16) 20. Qg4 ({
What is wrong with} 20. Qh5 $2 f5 $1 {Now, we cannot take en passant since our
queen is under attack.}) 20... Qg8 21. Rf3 Rf8 22. Rf4 Qh7 {Black has found a
good defensive setup, with a complicated positional battle to follow.} 23. Be3
Rac8 24. Nf1 Nd8 25. Nd2 Rc2 26. b3 Rc3 27. Qh5 Qc2 28. Qe2 Nc6 29. g3 Qd3 30.
Qh5 Kg8 31. Ne4 $5 {An amazing idea! White cuts off Black's queen from the
kingside with a knight sacrifice.} dxe4 32. Rg4 $44 Rc8 33. Bxh6 Kf8 $2 (33...
Bf8) 34. Rxg7 Ke8 35. Qxf7+ (35. Rxf7 $3 $18) 35... Kd7 36. Be3 Re8 $15 37. h5
Nxd4 38. Kg2 Nf5 39. h6 Rcc8 40. Rg6 Qd5 41. Rxe6 Rc6 42. Qxf5 Rxe6 43. Qg4
Qxe5 44. Bf4 Qf6 45. Rxe4 Bd6 46. h7 Bxf4 47. Rxf4 Qe5 48. Rf7+ Kc8 49. Qf3 Qe4
50. Qxe4 Rxe4 51. Rxa7 Kb8 52. Rg7 Rh8 53. g4 Rxh7 54. Rxh7 Rxg4+ 55. Kf3 Rd4
56. Ke3 Rd6 57. Rh4 Rb6 58. Rc4 Kb7 59. f4 Ka6 60. f5 Ka5 61. Rc5+ 1-0

