1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Nxd7 5. O-O Ngf6 6. Qe2 Rc8 7. c3 ({
The flexible} 7. d3 {is also possible. For example} e6 (7... g6 8. c3) 8. a4
Be7 9. b3 O-O 10. Bb2 Nb8 11. Nfd2) 7... e6 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 10. e5 Ne4 {
The are some differences compared to the main line with 4...Qxd7: White's
queen is on e2 and Black's queen's knight is on d7.} 11. Be3 Rc6 (11... Be7 12.
Ne1 h6 (12... O-O $2 13. f3 Ng5 14. h4 $18 {[%csl Rg5]}) 13. f3 Ng5 14. Nd3 O-O
15. Nc3 (15. Nd2)) 12. Ne1 $5 {Threatening to win the knight with f3.} f5 13.
Nd3 {This is pretty much the only position in which ...f5 is not met with exf6
e.p.} Be7 14. f3 Ng5 15. Nd2 $16 {[%csl Rg5]} O-O 16. Rfc1 Nb8 17. b4 Rxc1+ 18.
Rxc1 Nc6 19. a3 {We do not necessarily want to play b5, but Nb3-Nc5.} Qd7 ({
However, we happily play b5 after} 19... a5 20. b5 Na7 21. a4 $16) 20. Nb3 a6
21. Ndc5 Qc8 22. b5 axb5 23. Qxb5 f4 24. Bf2 Bxc5 25. Nxc5 Qa8 26. a4 h6 27. h4
Nh7 $18 {Black resigned since e6 is dropping.} 1-0

